  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0db6\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd9\u0db8\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "This is how schools will be held next week",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry has decided to hold schools during the week from 27th June 2022 to 1st July 2022 as follows.",
        "1. Schools which do not have transport facilities for students and teachers should be maintained as usual from 2020/06/20 to 2022/06/24 from 20222/06/24 as in schools in rural schools. Free and flexible schedules are set.",
        "2. Schools in urban areas which were not held last week should be held 3 days a week i.e. on Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays from 07.30 am to 01.30 pm. In these schools too, the principal has the power to decide on the number of days that the primary sections will be held.",
        "Learning activities are continued through online teaching / assignments / home-based activities for students' non-attendance days.",
        "3. This day will not be considered as a private holiday for teachers who do not attend school due to transportation difficulties.",
        "4. The Ministry of Education pays tribute to all the principals and teachers who contributed to the running of the school amidst transport difficulties from 20/206/206 to 2022/06/24."
      ],
